{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, using a seeded extractor for random number generation demands a (near-)perfectly random seed as the resource, which leads to a circularity.",
    "As in the QKD example, using Cryptomite we introduce a min-entropy rate parameter r that allows the extractor seed to be weakly random only, whilst still outputting near-perfect randomness.",
    "The code for this extension can be found in Figure 8. import cryptomite from math import floor, log2 def randomness_extraction(raw_randomness: list, seed_bits: list, n_1 = 6500000000, epsilon = 10**-10, k_1 = 581295000) \"\"\" Perform randomness extraction for the RNG protocol.",
    "Parameters ----------raw_randomness: list of bits, the outcomes of measurements.",
    "seed_bits: list of bits, generated independently."
  ]
}